# Implementation Plan: Scroll Performance Optimization

The user reported that the site feels "heavy" and doesn't move smoothly when scrolling. My investigation has identified several GPU-intensive CSS patterns that are the likely causes of this "jank" (dropped frames).

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> To improve performance significantly, I propose reducing the glassmorphism blur intensity and potentially disabling it on mobile devices. This will change the visual look slightly but will result in a much smoother experience.

## Proposed Changes

### Core Styles & Optimization

#### [MODIFY] [global.css](file:///c:/Users/user/Downloads/txt file/Ascreative/src/styles/global.css)
- Reduce `--glass-blur` from `16px` to `12px` (or `8px` on mobile) to lower the GPU cost of `backdrop-filter`.
- Add `will-change: transform, opacity;` to `.fade-in-up` to hardware-accelerate scroll animations.
- Add `will-change: transform;` to `.blob` elements in the ambient background.
- Add `content-visibility: auto; contain-intrinsic-size: 1px 1000px;` to the `.section` class to skip rendering off-screen content.
- Ensure all hover states use `transform: translate3d()` to prevent layout shifts.

#### [MODIFY] [Layout.astro](file:///c:/Users/user/Downloads/txt file/Ascreative/src/layouts/Layout.astro)
- Throttling the scroll event listener for the navbar to reduce execution frequency.
- Adding a `pointer-events: none` safety to the `.ambient-bg` to ensure it doesn't interfere with interaction (already present, but will verify).

#### [MODIFY] [Hero.astro](file:///c:/Users/user/Downloads/txt file/Ascreative/src/components/Hero.astro)
- Optimize the `.hero-scanlines` animation (ensure it's using GPU-friendly properties).
- Add `will-change: transform;` to any animated hero elements.

### Content Visibility
- Apply `content-visibility: auto` to major sections in `index.astro`, `about.astro`, etc., to reduce the total number of elements the browser needs to track during a long scroll (the page is 5000px high).

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run `npm run build` to ensure no regressions.
- Use the browser subagent to measure FPS during scroll after the fix.

### Manual Verification
- Verify the "heaviness" is gone on both desktop and mobile viewports.
- Ensure the glassmorphism aesthetic is still preserved.
